  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Most location services are meant to be used while your app is in the foreground, but some can also run in the background or even cause your app to be launched. To receive events in the background, configure the Location updates capability for your app in Xcode, as shown in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "link-media-2904072"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". You must also set the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/cllocationmanager/1620568-allowsbackgroundlocationupdates"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of your "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/cllocationmanager"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2904072",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2904072",
                "title": "Figure 1",
                "abstract": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Enabling background location updates"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When the system launches your app, use the launch options dictionary passed to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiapplicationdelegate/1623032-application"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiapplicationdelegate/1622921-application"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " methods to determine whether your app was launched to handle a location update. This dictionary contains the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiapplicationlaunchoptionslocationkey"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " key when the app is launched because of location services. Create a new "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/cllocationmanager"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object, configure it with a delegate, and start location services again to receive the update. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/getting_the_user_s_location/handling_location_events_in_the_background#2865362"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " lists the services that launch your app to report new location updates. Services that cause an app to be relaunched do so even after the user force-quits the app"
            }
          ]
        },
